It was, in one word, an octopus. One word was misleading, however. It was in actuality an eight storey tall translucent octopus, containing a seven storey tall translucent octopus, containing a six storey tall translucent octopus, //et cetera.// Six of its tentacles dipped down into the gelatin, and when they moved the landscape shifted dramatically. Two of them were free; they stretched away to practical infinity.

Something, presumably the octopus, suddenly spoke in a high and querulous tone. [[span class="THBBBBTTHBBBBTTHBBBBT"]]WHO SUMMONED ME?"[[/span]]

Udo traded a glance with her father, lying beside her in the bed of gel. She crossed her legs. "Uh. My name is Udo? This is my dad." This felt somehow insufficient. "His name is Obi." Still not quite enough. "Hello?"

[[span class="THBBBBTTHBBBBTTHBBBBT"]]HELLO![[/span]] it trilled back. [[span class="THBBBBTTHBBBBTTHBBBBT"]]I AM THE EIGHTLIEGE, THE AFTER-JUDGE OF THE MOLLUSCARI, THE PRINCE OF SUNKEN CREPUSC. MY TRUE NAME IS //THBBBBT THBBBBT THBBBBT.// MAYHAP YOU HAVE HEARD IT SPOKEN?[[/span]]

Udo reckoned she'd heard no less than three separate toddlers speak the name of the Prince of Sunken Crepusc on at least three different occasions. She also reckoned it unwise to say so. "I come from a wretched, benighted realm," she said instead, "where even the light of one so immensely... immense as yourself cannot reach." If she'd been standing up, she might have curtsied -- though she didn't trust the length of her labcoat. She did smile demurely as she attempted to stand up, plunging one arm into the sparkling surface.

The octopus-thing clapped the butts of its two free tentacles together excitedly. [[span class="THBBBBTTHBBBBTTHBBBBT"]]OH, WOW, THAT WAS GREAT. WE DID THE FANCY SPEECH THING! I'VE ALWAYS WANTED TO DO THE FANCY SPEECH THING.[[/span]]

Her smile became manic as she stumbled to her feet. "Yeah, that was neat. Very Ben Jonson." She helped her father up.

[[span class="THBBBBTTHBBBBTTHBBBBT"]]BEN WHO? THE SPRINTER? I DON'T GET THE REFERENCE.[[/span]]

Her cheeks hurt now. "No, ah, the playwright? Spelled different." She blinked. "Okay. Are we cool? You and me, and him?" She made a complex 'you and me and him' gesture, as if it would help. //Lord, don't let that be a spell.//

[[span class="THBBBBTTHBBBBTTHBBBBT"]]YEAH, OF COURSE WE'RE COOL.[[/span]] The skyscraper-sized cephalopod listed wildly to one side. [[span class="THBBBBTTHBBBBTTHBBBBT"]]WHY WOULDN'T WE BE COOL?[[/span]]

Udo shrugged, and looked at her father again. He shrugged.

[[span class="THBBBBTTHBBBBTTHBBBBT"]]IT'S THE GIANT OCTOPUS THING, RIGHT? RIGHT, OF COURSE IT IS.[[/span]] Several of the interior octopi grew noticeably smaller, then noticeably larger; she wondered if they were breathing, and if they were really an 'it'. She decided not to think about it.

//Thbbbbt Thbbbbt Thbbbbt// was still talking. [[span class="THBBBBTTHBBBBTTHBBBBT"]]RULE OF THUMB FOR CORBENIC: YOU'LL KNOW YOU'RE NOT COOL WITH SOMEONE WHEN THEY STRAIGHT-UP MURDER YOU. AFTERLIFES WITH NEAR-INSTANT REGENERATION ARE GREAT FOR PEOPLE BEING VERY HONEST AND EXPLICIT WITH THEIR FEELINGS.[[/span]]

"Mm." Udo furrowed her brow. "Not sure I'd like to test that regeneration during, you know, the death of magic."

[[span class="THBBBBTTHBBBBTTHBBBBT"]]OH, DO THEY HAVE THAT WHERE YOU'RE FROM? I WAS GONNA SAY, IF YOU DON'T, GIVE IT A PASS. IT'S BEEN PLAYING MERRY HELL WITH MY SINUSES.[[/span]]

"Your sinuses," Obi repeated.

[[span class="THBBBBTTHBBBBTTHBBBBT"]]YEAH, THERE USED TO BE A THAUMATURGIC MEMBRANE KEEPING ALL THE GEL FROM GOING UP MY NOSE WHEN I BREATHE. PART OF THE WHOLE 'SURE, WE'VE BANISHED YOU UNDERGROUND FOR A FORTNIGHT, BUT WE'RE NOT TRYING TO ACTUALLY TORTURE YOU' DEALIO.[[/span]]

Udo looked down at the gel. She could swear she saw the refracted silhouette of the kangaroo, bounding downward into the depths. "You were banished? Why?"

[[span class="THBBBBTTHBBBBTTHBBBBT"]]DON'T REMEMBER.[[/span]] Somehow the giant octopus gave the vague impression of a shrug. [[span class="THBBBBTTHBBBBTTHBBBBT"]]BIT OF INTER-PANTHEONIC INTRIGUE, BIT OF BACKSTABBING, HAVE YOUR AVATARS DUKE IT OUT, AND WHAMMO. SOMEBODY GETS SENT TO THE DEPTHS OF THE GELATE WASTES TO RUMINATE ON HIS OR HER FAILURE.[[/span]] The voice yawned, somehow, in their minds. [[span class="THBBBBTTHBBBBTTHBBBBT"]]I WONDER IF THE TERM'S UP YET. YOU HEAR FROM THOSE LUNAR DAWN GUYS RECENTLY?[[/span]]

Udo's eyes widened. "Lunar Dawn? You mean the Three Moons Initiative? They haven't been called that for..." She frowned. "For like... forever."

[[span class="THBBBBTTHBBBBTTHBBBBT"]]OH. LONGER THAN A FORTNIGHT?[[/span]]

"Yes," Obi said. "Longer than a fortnight."

[[span class="THBBBBTTHBBBBTTHBBBBT"]]WELL __THAT'S__ BULLSHIT.[[/span]] The ground quaked as the angry octopus thrashed helplessly. [[span class="THBBBBTTHBBBBTTHBBBBT"]]I THOUGHT FOR SURE THEY'D REMEMBER AFTER A FIFTNIGHT AT THE LATEST! I'VE HALF A MIND TO GO GIVE THEM WHAT-FOR IN THEIR SKY FORTRESS.[[/span]] It wriggled back and forth in the gel, trying in vain to free its remaining six limbs. [[span class="THBBBBTTHBBBBTTHBBBBT"]]MIGHT TAKE ME A CENTURY OR TWO, MIND YOU.[[/span]]

Obi placed a hand on his daughter's shoulder. "I know someone who can help with that."

She stared at him. "You do?"

