The inlaid maple door was mostly ajar, which was good. She wrested it the rest of the way open, and was rewarded with a rush of thin red liquid. It trickled down the marble steps to pool around her stitched leather boots. Her first thought was that it was blood. Her second thought was more sensible.

[[span class="BlackLord"]]**AT THE TAPS AGAIN, I SEE.**[[/span]]

There was a stirring in the candle-lit murk. [[span class="RedLord"]]**CROSS THE THRESHOLD,**[[/span]] a burst of liquid lasciviousness demanded. [[span class="RedLord"]]**AND SHUT THE DOOR. YOU'RE LETTING ALL THE CLARET OUT.**[[/span]]

She walked into the brothel, and obliged enough to stop the flow but not enough to trigger Alagadda's ejector seat when she eventually left. The floor was panelled with redwood, the widest boards she'd ever seen, as though the better part of California had been chopped down to finish this single tremendous space. There was a polished bar as long as... as long as her gaze could travel, functionally endless like the columns in the Odion. There were hundreds of upright tables, hundreds more upside-down on top of them or flat against the wine-dark floor, shattered glass and porcelain everywhere, scattered barrels and tablecloths and chairs. The ceiling was a mirror of the floor, minus the wrack... although even as the thought occurred to her, she watched a single metal fork fall down to splash in the pool of plum.

[[span class="RedLord"]]**GRAVITY IS SUCH A BITCH.**[[/span]] The telepathic drunkard actually hiccoughed in her ear. [[span class="RedLord"]]**SERVES US RIGHT FOR WALKING ON THE CEILINGS, I SUPPOSE.**[[/span]]

The Red Lord was seated across the boundless saloon at a large round table with a stained red cloth. A veritable mountain of varnished barrels, all of them slowly leaking, were piled up behind it. Its grinning mask beamed blearily at her as she approached.

[[span class="RedLord"]]**HAVE YOU COME FOR THE FUN? I WISH YOU'D COME EARLIER.**[[/span]] It ran its ink blot eyes up and down her dress, nodding in shaky approval. [[span class="RedLord"]]**OH, YES, I WISH YOU __HAD__ COME EARLIER.**[[/span]]

"Drinking alone?" She affected a haughty pose, hands on hips, right leg stuck provocatively out of the obscene dress. Her mind, in the end, was a tactical one. "Hardly suits your reputation."

The Red Lord laughed in her face, or rather in her head, a deep and throaty baying like a hound in desperate heat. [[span class="RedLord"]]**YOU'RE A DELECTABLE LITTLE BALL OF CURVES AND MUSCLE, AREN'T YOU? MAYBE I SHOULD LET YOU TAKE THAT PENT-UP ENERGY OUT ON ME. IT'S POSSIBLE WE'D BOTH ENJOY IT.**[[/span]] It growled, and the image of a hungry wolf solidified in her mind's eye. [[span class="RedLord"]]**IT'S POSSIBLE ONLY I WOULD, BUT THAT'S A RISK I'M USUALLY WILLING TO TAKE.**[[/span]]

She flipped over an upended chair, tossed away the wine-soaked cushion and sat down. "I'm very particular who I party with."

It waved its sleeves dismissively. [[span class="RedLord"]]**THE JUBILEE IS ENDED IN ALAGADDA, MORSEL, AND ACROSS THE REALMS OF MEN AND MADNESS BOTH.**[[/span]] It paused. [[span class="RedLord"]]**WHAT ARE YOU, ANYWAY? YOU LOOK HUMAN, BUT THEN, I'M SEEING DOUBLE.**[[/span]]

She shook her head. //He's plastered. If he didn't have a key, we wouldn't even need to roll this asshole.//

The Red Lord's grin widened dangerously. [[span class="RedLord"]]**WE. WHO IS WE?**[[/span]] The mask squinted. [[span class="RedLord"]]**MY MEMORY'S NOT WHAT IT ONCE WAS, THANKFULLY, BUT I REMEMBER HUMANS AS A NON-PLURAL FORM OF LIFE.**[[/span]]

"Sure, I'm human." She returned the lascivious grin. "How about you? Where it counts."

That uproarious, untrustworthy laughter leaked out again. [[span class="RedLord"]]**I HAVE MY WEAKNESSES, IF THAT'S WHAT YOU MEAN. WINE, WOMEN, SONG.**[[/span]] Its eyes flickered scarlet, just for a moment. [[span class="RedLord"]]**HAVE YOU BEEN TO THE ODIUM? I HAD TICKETS, BUT THEN, I ALSO HAD __STANDARDS__.**[[/span]]

She laughed, and it wasn't entirely an affectation. "Happy to hear it. Do those standards extend to your cellar?" She pointed at the barrelfall. "I wouldn't mind a drink, assuming that's wine and not blood."

The Red Lord shrugged, plucking a pair of flagons off the floor and staggering to its invisible feet. [[span class="RedLord"]]**IT'S WINE,**[[/span]] it slurred. [[span class="RedLord"]]**BUT THAT DOESN'T MEAN IT ISN'T ALSO BLOOD.**[[/span]]

She rolled her shoulders as it poured out a copious quantity. "Where do you find enough..."

It smirked, ear to bloodless ear. [[span class="RedLord"]]**ENOUGH //RUBEDO?// COME NOW, SURELY YOU ALREADY HAVE THE ANSWER.**[[/span]]

The barrels, she suddenly realized, were much larger than they needed to be. The silence of the streets outside oppressed her with their ugly import. She swallowed, and stood up. "I don't suppose you have anything in here which started out life on a vine?"

The Red Lord shrugged, and dropped the second mug to the sopping boards. [[span class="RedLord"]]**I RUN AN EQUITABLE ESTABLISHMENT. THERE'S SURE TO BE WEAKER SPIRITS IN STOCK, FOR WEAKER SPIRITS LIKE YOURS.**[[/span]]

She found a black bottle with white stencilling behind the bar: Cháteau Lafite, 1787. "You weren't joking."

[[span class="RedLord"]]**NOT ALWAYS, BUT OFTEN.**[[/span]] 

When she returned to the table, the Lord was already hunched over its mug. She sat down again and ripped the top off the bottle. "To your health?"

[[span class="RedLord"]]**HARDLY.**[[/span]] It glared at her. [[span class="RedLord"]]**YOU WANT SOMETHING, WHOEVER YOU ARE, AND I AM NOT THE GIVING SORT. I TAKE, YOU SEE, I __TAKE__, AND I TAKE THAT WHICH IS NOT OFFERED MOST OF ALL.**[[/span]] It leaned back, and she could see the leathery darkness beneath its robes expanding and contracting with rapid breath. [[span class="RedLord"]]**WHAT DO YOU WANT FROM ME, YOU IMBECILIC BEAUTY, AND WHAT DO YOU FEAR TO LOSE?**[[/span]] It clasped its robed hands around its drink.

She lifted the bottle to her lips. "I want your key," she said, and took a swig. She was surprised and relieved to find that the bottle of red wine contained, in fact, red wine. "Give me that, and you can take what you want. //After// you drink." She wiped her lips off on her dress sleeve.

The lord was virtually vibrating in its seat as it placed the flagon to its sneering graven lips. [[span class="RedLord"]]**WE ARE GOING TO ADORE YOU.**[[/span]] Its eyes burned wine-red as it downed the rubedo in one gulp. [[span class="RedLord"]]**YOU ARE NOT GOING TO ENJOY IT.**[[/span]]

[[span class="BlackLord"]]**POOR, STUPID RUDY.**[[/span]] The Red Lord froze as the loathsome murmur swelled. [[span class="BlackLord"]]**YOU'VE SUNK TO THE OCCASION MAGNIFICENTLY, HAVEN'T YOU?**[[/span]]

It staggered to its feet, looking down at her with a complex mix of mocked emotions. [[span class="RedLord"]]**OH. OH, I SEE. THE BILL HAS COME DUE AT LAST.**[[/span]] It pushed past her, nearly upsetting the table in its haste. [[span class="RedLord"]]**MY CUE TO LEAVE.**[[/span]]

[[span class="BlackLord"]]**ALWAYS THE LAST TO QUIT THE PARTY, OLD FRIEND.**[[/span]] The Red Lord stumbled, slipped in the roseate plashet, and looked back at her with an expression of confused terror.

[[span class="RedLord"]]**IT'S MY NATURE,**[[/span]] it gasped, before its orifices ran black and it fell forward into the wasted drink.

[[span class="BlackLord"]]**HE KEEPS HIS KEY IN THE TILL,**[[/span]] the cruel voice yawned. [[span class="BlackLord"]]**DRUNKS ARE SO PREDICTABLE.**[[/span]]

"You could have told me that at the start," she groused, heading for the bar again. "Saved me a bit of tension."

[[span class="BlackLord"]]**TENSION? PAH. THERE WAS NOTHING TO IT.**[[/span]] The gilded register did indeed conceal a red-rusted key. [[span class="BlackLord"]]**SLAUGHTER INTO WINE, AND BACK AGAIN. BASIC AS ALCHEMY GETS.**[[/span]]


