The aperture remained open as Udo dropped the filthy robe on the filthy floor and embraced her friend. Her father watched for a moment, then turned and walked away.

"Stupid plan," Udo sobbed. "Stupid, //stupid// plan."

"Was that your dad?" Ibanez didn't know what else to say. "Why... why?"

Udo shook her head. "Not now. We don't have time."

[[span class="BlackLord"]]**OH, YOU KNEW? I WAS HOPING TO SURPRISE YOU.**[[/span]]

The Black Lord stood beside the throne where the Hanged King was slumped, unresponsive. A myriad of tiny, faceless creatures were pulling chains and singed ropes across its motionless body. [[span class="BlackLord"]]**DIMENSIONAL TRAVEL IS SO VERY DRAINING. MY LIEGE-LORD NEEDS HIS REST.**[[/span]]

Udo sneered as they approached the daïs. "I thought you were the faithful one."

The tragedy mask affected a look of wounded dignity. [[span class="BlackLord"]]**I AM, I AM! THEY WOULD HAVE LET HIM ROT FOR ALL ETERNITY. I ONLY PLAN TO TAKE THE LEAD FOR, OH, SHALL WE SAY AN AEON OR TWO?**[[/span]] Two quivering figures stepped into the light, standing behind the Ambassador's stolen body. One in red, the other in yellow. Their masks were caked in opaque ectoplasm. [[span class="BlackLord"]]**WE'RE ALL ON THE SAME PAGE, NOW. LET'S DO SOME EXPLORING.**[[/span]] It eyed the portal hungrily.

"Well, you're welcome." Ibanez kicked at the grime on the floor, exposing cracks in the mortar. "Don't call us, yadda yadda."

[[span class="BlackLord"]]**WHY WOULD I NEED TO CALL YOU?**[[/span]] The tragic scowl returned. [[span class="BlackLord"]]**YOU'RE NOT GOING ANYWHERE.**[[/span]]

"I could seal the aperture," Udo growled, stuffing her hands into her pockets. "Don't test me."

[[span class="BlackLord"]]**I HAVE WORN ENOUGH MORTALS TO KNOW BETTER,**[[/span]] the Black Lord laughed. [[span class="BlackLord"]]**YOU WOULD LOSE SO MUCH IF YOU SHUT THAT DOOR. YOU WOULD NEVER BE ABLE TO OPEN IT AGAIN. THAT WHICH IS DEAD--**[[/span]] 

"Everything dies," Udo snarled. "Go fuck yourself."

"That's not very poetic," Ibanez chided. "I think you mean 'shut your trap'."

The Black Lord lunged, and Udo chucked two fistfuls of Corbenic sand into its oily face. The aperture snapped shut, Ibanez clapped her hands, the door in the floor under centuries of dust and dried tears dropped open beneath them and they fell into another world. 

Theirs.

The Black Lord wiped its face clean, then flicked a mass of bituminous sand onto the walls. [[span class="BlackLord"]]**OH, WELL. BRAVO.**[[/span]]

